                           Directory Contents - /


  doc/
    Lots of IMPORTANT DOCUMENTATION that you MUST READ is in this directory.

  help/
    All of the bot's help files are stored here.

  language/
    All of the bot's language files are stored here.

  logs/
    This is a good place for eggdrop to store log files.

  misc/
    These are misc. source/script files.

  scripts/
    Tcl scripts included with Eggdrop are contained in this directory.
    Also contains conf2toml.py, a migration tool for converting old .conf
    files to the new TOML format.

  src/
    This is the Eggdrop source.

  text/
    This contains the motd and banner files.

  AUTHORS
    Contains a list of Eggdrop developers and major contributors.

  ChangeLog.gz
    Contains git commit logs from each change made to Eggdrop in the git
    repository (compressed).

  CONTENTS
    This file.

  COPYING
    Eggdrop legal information is contained in this file.

  disabled_modules
    Any module listed in this file will not be compiled by default.

  eggdrop.toml  (PRIMARY — modern TOML format)
    The complete configuration reference. Every available setting is
    documented with its default value and a description, organised into
    readable sections ([bot], [servers], [channels], [modules], ...).
    Use this as a reference or start your own config with:
      eggdrop --setup mybot.toml

  eggdrop-basic.toml  (PRIMARY — modern TOML format)
    A minimal, ready-to-edit TOML config covering only the most commonly
    needed settings. Recommended starting point for new installs.

  eggdrop.conf  (source only — not installed)
    The original Tcl-script configuration reference, kept in the source
    tree for reference only. It is no longer installed with the bot.
    The bot still accepts .conf files when passed explicitly on the
    command line for users who have existing configs.

  eggdrop-basic.conf  (source only — not installed)
    A minimal Tcl-script configuration kept in the source tree for
    reference only. Not installed with the bot.

  FEATURES
    This tells you what Eggdrop can do -- a kind of advertisement.

  INSTALL
    Information on installing your Eggdrop, including build instructions
    and the quick-start guide for the new TOML configuration format.

  NEWS
    This lists significant differences with previous versions.

  README
    You should read this file before even trying to compile Eggdrop.

  ssl.conf
    An OpenSSL config file, used for generating SSL certificates.
    See doc/TLS for details.

  THANKS
    Contains a full list of Eggdrop contributors.

  UPGRADING
    Contains information on upgrading from older Eggdrop versions,
    including a migration guide from .conf (Tcl) to .toml (TOML).
